cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper is about a meta-algorithm for machine learning that guarantees correctness by using refusals. It is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with improving the accuracy of prediction algorithms. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing an algorithm that can make decisions based on data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves developing a new algorithm for processing data. It could also be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it has practical applications in various fields. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it involves ensuring correctness and robustness in machine learning algorithms.
